summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of several banks, ranked by a numerical "Score." Long Island Trust leads with a score of 7.0, followed closely by Chemical and Citibank, both achieving 6.7. National Bank of North America and Chase Manhattan are positioned next, with identical scores of 6.6. European American bank is at the lower end of this ranking, with a score of 6.4. The structure is a simple, ordered list, indicating a performance or rating comparison across these financial institutions.
